column2: Sunny- calm- level is down compared to last year
Near perfect conditions- calm- sunny.  Water level: Up 2-3"
Ice cleared the lake Easter Sunday- 4-19.  Clear- calm- sunny. Water level: Up 6-8 inches
Some pollen. Sunny and clear with mirror-like surface.
Sunny day- following rain. Water level: up 10-12"
Partly sunny- some breeze- storm with hard rain in past 24 hours.
Sunny- with some wind to cause a choppy surface.
Perfect day for taking a reading- sunny and surface was like a mirror. Water level up 1"
Conditions near perfect for maximum reading.
Ice off- 4-19-93- clear to hazy day- calm.  Water level: up 2" abov last
Clear- calm- sunny- near perfect conditions
First day of sunshine in a week- slight breeze.
Calm- cloudy- first good reading possible in past 2 weeks.  Water level:up 2" from last reading
Bright- calm period at time of reading
Partly cloudy and windy enough to hold boat from drifting
Partly sunny- slight wind from the south.
Overcast- slight wind- some chop on surface
Partially overcast- some sun- very slight wind.
Bright sunny day- clear with slight breeze- temp is 60 degrees.
Very hot- 94 degrees in the sun- 86 degrees in the shade- bright and some haze- calm.
Weather is clear- sunny- NW wind made it difficult to sample.
Bright sun- more windy than normal.  Lake level: very high
The water is blue green. near perfect sampling conditions.  Clear- bright- and no wind.  Rain gauge reading from 7/21 to 7/24 = 2 to 2.5 inches.
Field temperature is 43 degrees.  Bright sun and slight wind.
Clear.  Slight wind.  Considerable pollen on surface.
Water level declining due to dry weather.  Air temp. 62 F.  No wind.  Sky cover 65%.
Air temp. 62 F.  2-4 mph wind from NE.
Calm and cloudy.  Lake dead calm with flat surface.
8-12 mph north wind.  Temp 70 F.  High thin clouds.
3 -5 mph breeze from west- 50% cloud cover- air temp 75F.
Wind calm- clear sky- air temp 72- appx. 1/2 hour before sunset
Sky clear- wind 5-7 mph- air temp 65F.  Another beautiful day.
NW Wind 8-12 mph- 50% cloud cover; air temp 57F.
Storm clearing- wind 10-14 mph air temp 58F- 50% cloud cover
Air temp 73 degrees F- wind 12-15 mph from SW- 60% cloud cover.
Air temp 78 F- 100% overcast with wind 3 -5 mph.
Air temp 80 F- wind 5 - 8 mph from NW-  sky 10% cloud cover.  Hit bottom at 54 feet.
Wind calm- sky clear- air temp 75F.  Rain two days previous.
Sky clear- air temp 75 F- winds calm.  Appx 1.5 inches rain over previous two days.
Air temp 72 degrees- wind calm- sky clear.  Approximately 4 inches of rain during previous week.  Lake level coming up.  This will be final test for year.
Air temp 64f- 50% cloud cover- wind 3-5 from SW.
Air temp 53f- 100% cloud cover with low overcast- wind 2-3 mph.  Many particulates floating in water column.  Anchored at 56' depth.
First use of digital temperature probe for measurements.  Air temp 60degrees- light cirrus cloud cover- wind 5-8 mph from north.
Sky 100% overcast- air temp 54f- wind calm.  Used digital temp probe.  No samples collected.
Overcast with scattered showers.  Air temp 65f- wind light and variable.  More than 3 inches of rain over previous 3 days.  Lake depth 56 feet at anchor site.
Air temp 74f- 50% cloud cover- wind calm.  Used van dorn sampler for temperature measurements.  Assisted by John Edward Leeb.

Air temp 70f- wind calm and water surface smooth.  Cloud cover 25% cumulus- 1/2 rain in last 2 weeks.  Assisted by John Leeb Jr.  Secchi readings 21.5- 22.0- 21.75.  Temp measurements with digital thermometer.
Air temp 79f- wind 10-12 knots- 25% cloud cover.  Appx. 0.2 inches of rain previous day.
Air temp 72f- sky clear and wind calm.  Assisted by W. Leeb
Air temp 70 degrees f- wind calm to 3 mph- 100% overcast.  Assisted by W. Leeb.  Another beautiful day
Air temp 73 f- wind 3-5 from SW- broken clouds.
Sky is clear- wind calm- air temp 79 degrees.  Assisted by Magdalen Leeb
Air temp 60 degrees f- wind 2-4 mph from northeast; sky overcast.  Cool overnight temperatures last several nights.
Assisted by Winifred Leeb.  Air temp 68f- wind calm and lake surface smooth.  Sky clear; another beautiful early fall day.  Final test of 2008 season for Leader Lake.
Light breeze- air temp 68F- assisted by Henry Beglinger
Air temp 60F- 100% overcast- wind dead calm- about 1.2" over previous two days.  Assisted by Winifred Leeb
Air temp 58F- wind NNW @ 3-6 mph- 100% cloud cover.
Air temp 70F- wind calm- 50% cloud cover.  Lake level low- no water flowing through Bond Lake channel.
Wind 1 -3 mph- 100% cloud cover with low overcast
Air temp 75F- partial cloud cover- light wind
Air temp 64F- 100% cloud cover- wind 3 - 5 mph from east.  Assisted by John Leeb and Claire Leeb
Air temp 72F- scattered clouds- wind calm.  Secchi readings taken 3x in bright sunlight: 20.0- 19.75- 20.0 ft.
Air temp 76F- widely scattered clouds- wind 5-7 mph from SE.
Air temp 75F- 40% cumulus cloud cover- wind 2-3 mph from northwest.  No rain for two weeks plus...   This will be the final data collection of summer 2009.
First monitoring of year 2010.  Weather has been cloudy and stormy past week- several inches of rain.  Today cloudy- air temp 72f- winds light from north at test time.
Air temp 64f- wind calm- partly cloudy.  A very nice day on the lake.  Assisted by Winifred Leeb.
Air temp 76F- wind 3-5 mph from west- 80% cloud cover.  Storms in area- but most are passing us by.
air temp 75f- wind 7-9 mph from west- sky clear and sunny.
Air temp 76f- wind calm- 100% cloud cover.
Temperature 73f- wind 3 - 5 mph from south- 10% cloud cover.  A beautiful day after a cool night (49F)
Air temp 74f- wind 2-3 mph from NE- 50% cloud cover- anchored in 49 feet of water.
Sky clear- wind 1-3 mph- air temp 70f; heavy pine and birch pollen drifting in air.  Two boats active on lake.   Assisted by W. Leeb
Wind calm- air temp 72F- sky clear.  Anchored at 53' depth.  Loon family has two chicks on lake this year.  New LaMotte chemicals for DO testing.
Air temp 76f- wind 2-3 mph from west- sky partly cloudy.  Many particulates in water column.
Air temp 75f- wind 5-8 mph from wsw- sky partly cloudy.
Air temp 76f- wind 5-7 from South- 10% cloud cover.  Anchored in 54' of water.  Assisted by John Leeb Jr.
Air temp 83f- 60% cumulus cloud cover- wind 2 - 5 mph from NNW.
Air temp 73f- wind calm- 50% cumulus cloud cover.  Secci readings 10'6"- 10'- 11'.
Temp 72f- wind 5-10 mph from northwest- mostly cloudy.  Assisted by Wendy Leeb.
Sky clear blue- air temp about 85f- wind 3-5 mph from west; anchored in 46 foot depth.
Assisted by Wendy Leeb Assisted by Wendy Leeb.  Monitored in center of north bay- approximately in front of Mathias home.

Partly sunny- temp 72f- light breeze from southeast.  Still some floating particulates in water column. Partly sunny- temp 72f- light breeze from southeast.  Still some floating particulates in water column.  Water level highest observed since mid 1960s.
Air temp 76F- 60% broken clouds.  Assisted by Joe Ryder- age 11
Air temp 72f- wind calm- 20% cloud cover- another gorgeous day
Air temp 72f- wind 2-4 mph from NW- 10% cloud cover.  Beautiful day.  One loon on the lake this afternoon.
Assisted by Winifred Leeb.  Calm wind- air temp 70f- another beautiful fall day.  No freeze yet!
Assisted by Beth Good.  Air temp 62f- thin clouds- SE breeze at 5 - 10 mph
Anchored at 56' depth!  Lake level is highest in my experience.  Air temp 75f- 10% scattered clouds- wind calm to 3 mph.  Assisted by Wendy Leeb

Assisted by Wendy Leeb.  Anchored at 56-57' depth!  Lake level is highest I have observed in 50+ years.  Air temp 75f- 10% scattered clouds- wind calm to 3 mph from west.  Recorded significant dissolved oxygen at all depths!
Assisted by Wendy Leeb.  Weather clear and sunny- 80f- light west breeze.  Several boats on lake.  Loons have two babies.
Assisted by Wendy Leeb.  Weather clear- calm and sunny.  Temperature about 74 f.
Assisted by Wendy Leeb; weather partly cloudy and 5 - 7 mph winds.  Several boats on the lake today
